This paper is about developing a learning rule for spiking neural networks to predict output firing behavior based on external stimulus. This falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which specifically deals with neural networks and their applications. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers a broad range of machine learning techniques including neural networks. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which also covers a broad range of AI techniques including neural networks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with control systems and their applications, including those based on neural networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), which deals with the complexity of algorithms and their applications, including those related to neural networks.
